                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.3311/177a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="to">Grew</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-03T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 3, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. The visit of the Japanese training squadron on the West Coast has been
                    satisfactorily completed, Navy Department and this <pb facs="0858" n="756"
                        xml:id="pg_756"/> Department are now considering advisability of a visit to
                    Japan by Commander-in-Chief Asiatic Fleet on flagship. Navy is ascertaining
                    Admiral’s present views. Department requests your views.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
